an act that manufactures food scarcity-to the social order of "world-class" cities, the pathways of discarded food as it circulates through the FNB kitchen, and the anticapitalist political movements the kitchen represents. Describing the mutual entanglement of global capitalism and anticapitalist transgression, Giles captures those emergent forms of generosity, solidarity, and resistance that spring from the global city's marginalized residents.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDumpster diving. 0aFood consumptionxSocial aspects. 0aFood security. 0aFood supplyxSocial aspects. 0aFood waste. 0aWaste (Economics)xSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aabject capitalism.  aneoliberal urban development.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478021711zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478021711423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478021711/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles